~ grammar / semantics checks (v0.0.8)

when (1 < 2) and (2 < 3):
    show "ok: a single comparison composes with 'and'"

~ 'and' binds tighter than 'or':  yes or (no and no) == yes
when yes or no and no:
    show "ok: and binds tighter than or"

~ iterating a map yields its KEYS (in insertion order)
make m = {a: 1, b: 2}
make ks = ""
for each k in m:
    set ks = ks + k
when ks == "ab":
    show "ok: for-each over a map yields keys"

~ repeat truncates a non-whole count toward zero
make c = 0
repeat 2.5 times:
    set c = c + 1
when c == 2:
    show "ok: repeat truncates 2.5 to 2"

~ set inserts a new map key; a bare key is the text of its name
make d = {}
set d["x"] = 1
when d["x"] == 1:
    show "ok: set inserts a new map key"
